The White House Press Secretary issued a statement on the 1000th day since American citizen Robert Levinson's disappearance in Iran. Levinson went missing on March 9, 2007, during a business trip to Kish Island. The United States government is urging the Iranian government to provide any information on Levinson's whereabouts and ensure his safe return to his family. General James L. Jones met with Levinson's family to assure them that his case remains a priority for the United States. Anyone with information is encouraged to contact the Department of State or the Levinson family via their website.